<subSubSection id="C3586572FF82FFFF0D3C1D4DFCA6FB87" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF82FFFF0D3C1D4DFF19FD62" blockId="15.[111,649,628,1700]" box="[113,213,628,654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF82FFFF0D3C1DADFE5AFC62" blockId="15.[111,649,628,1700]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">
This species belongs to a group of ellipsoid-fruited taxa that inhabit the dry forests of western and northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3557669FF82FFFF0D9A1DEAFE9BFD03" box="[215,343,723,749]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Others in this group include the widely distributed 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0C121DCAFE1CFCE3" box="[351,464,755,781]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0C121DCAFE1CFCE3" box="[351,464,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the localized endemics 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0D911C2AFE0EFCC3" authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" box="[220,450,787,813]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="buxifolium">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D911C2AFEB8FCC3" box="[220,372,787,813]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. buxifolium</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0CBA1C2AFF66FCA2" authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multinode">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CBA1C2AFD4AFCC3" box="[503,646,787,813]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. multinode</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
-Fél. Additional characters shared by these species are their coriaceous leaves drying brownish and their deciduous bracts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF82FFFF0DC51CA8FDE5FA08" blockId="15.[111,649,628,1700]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF0DC51CA8FEF5FC45" author="DANGUY P." box="[136,313,913,939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" pagination="544 - 546" refId="ref9886" refString="DANGUY P. 1922. - Contribution a l'etude des melastomacees de Madagascar. Comptes rendus de l'Association francaise pour l'Avancement des Sciences 45: 544 - 546 (dated 1921, published 1922)." type="journal article" year="1922">Danguy (1922)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0CFB1CABFDFCFC42" box="[438,560,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CFB1CABFDFCFC42" box="[438,560,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single flowering collection (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CEF1C88FDE5FC25" box="[418,553,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Perrier 1048</emphasis>
, P), but the taxonomy of this species has been in a confused state ever since. This is mainly because the species concept of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF0DA11B29FDC5FBC4" author="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H." box="[236,521,1040,1066]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref10125" refString="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H. 1932. - Les Melastomacees de Madagascar. Memoires de l'Academie malgache 12: 1 - 292, 10 pls." type="book chapter" year="1932">Perrier de la Bâthie (1932</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF0F5B1B29FD83FBC4" author="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H." box="[534,591,1040,1066]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" refId="ref10152" refString="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H. 1951. - Melastomatacees, in HUMBERT H. (ed.), Flore de Madagascar, 153. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 326 p." type="book" year="1951">1951</bibRefCitation>
) was based on discordant elements. He described the fruits of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0D861B69FEF2FB84" box="[203,318,1104,1130]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D861B69FEF2FB84" box="[203,318,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as oblong (
<quantity id="4CBA9B1CFF82FFFF0CFA1B76FDC9FB87" box="[439,517,1103,1129]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B1CFF82FFFF0F0A1B76FD4AFB87" box="[583,646,1103,1129]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide), but his circumscription included specimens in which the fruits are ellipsoid (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0C9B1BB6FD8CFB47" box="[470,576,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Perrier 32</emphasis>
, P) or globose (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D801B96FE89FB27" box="[205,325,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Pervillé 542</emphasis>
, P). Jacques-Félix (1985b) later characterized the fruit of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0C231BF7FE16FB06" box="[366,474,1230,1256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0C231BF7FE16FB06" box="[366,474,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as globose, again based on 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D961BD7FE96FAE6" box="[219,346,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Pervillé 542</emphasis>
(which is furthermore part of the original material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0CCB1A37FDB7FAC6" authority="Naudin" authorityName="Naudin" box="[390,635,1294,1320]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtiforme">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CCB1A37FDD2FAC6" box="[390,542,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. myrtiforme</emphasis>
Naudin
</taxonomicName>
). Although the proper determination of the 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0F741A14FD4AFAA9" box="[569,646,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Pervillé</emphasis>
specimen remains unclear, it is entirely different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0DE31A54FEEDFA69" box="[174,289,1389,1415]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0DE31A54FEEDFA69" box="[174,289,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and must be excluded from that species. It is also different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0CA91AB5FD4AFA48" box="[484,646,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtiforme">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CA91AB5FD4AFA48" box="[484,646,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. myrtiforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(lectotypified by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF0C7C1A95FE24FA28" author="WICKENS G. E." box="[305,488,1452,1478]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10377" refString="WICKENS G. E. 1976. - Notes on Terminalia (Combretaceae) and Memecylon (Melastomataceae) for the &quot; Flore des Mascareignes &quot;. Kew Bulletin 31: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1976">Wickens [1976]</bibRefCitation>
, based on 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0F2E1A95FEEBFA08" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Du Petit-Thouars s.n.</emphasis>
, P, barcode no. 62664).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF82FFFF0DC51AD2FC6EFDFE" blockId="15.[111,649,628,1700]" lastBlockId="15.[674,1212,216,1129]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">
As now conceived, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0C131AD5FE18F9E8" box="[350,468,1516,1542]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0C131AD5FE18F9E8" box="[350,468,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes several specimens with fruits that are clearly ellipsoid (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D371912FF2AF9AB" box="[122,230,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Perrier 32</emphasis>
, P; 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0C581912FDB3F9AB" box="[277,639,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Herb. Jard. Bot. Tananarive 6171</emphasis>
, P; 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0DC31972FEF5F98B" box="[142,313,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Humbert 32555</emphasis>
, MO, P; 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0CD21972FDA7F98B" box="[415,619,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Rahanyamalala s.n.</emphasis>
in 1990, P; 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0D941953FE91F96A" box="[217,349,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Schatz 2989</emphasis>
, CAS, MO, P; 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0F421953FF65F94A" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Noyes et al. 1070</emphasis>
, MO, P). Its circumscription also includes all of the material previously assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF097D1FE0FC8CFEFC" authority="H. Perrier. The" authorityName="H. Perrier. The" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ankarense">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF097D1FE0FB75FF1D" box="[1072,1209,217,243]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. ankarense</emphasis>
H.Perrier. The
</taxonomicName>
fruit of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0ED01FC1FBE5FEFC" box="[925,1065,248,274]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ankarense">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0ED01FC1FBE5FEFC" box="[925,1065,248,274]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. ankarense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been described as globose and 
<quantity id="4CBA9B1CFF82FFFF0ED81E21FC2FFEDC" box="[917,995,280,306]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
in diameter (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF093D1E21FC90FEBF" author="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H." pageId="15" pageNumber="352" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref10125" refString="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H. 1932. - Les Melastomacees de Madagascar. Memoires de l'Academie malgache 12: 1 - 292, 10 pls." type="book chapter" year="1932">Perrier de la Bâthie 1932</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B08FF82FFFF0E2B1E0EFC6CFEBF" author="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H." box="[870,928,311,337]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" refId="ref10152" refString="PERRIER DE LA BATHIE H. 1951. - Melastomatacees, in HUMBERT H. (ed.), Flore de Madagascar, 153. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 326 p." type="book" year="1951">1951</bibRefCitation>
; Jacques-Félix 1985b), but this was based on a single example in very poor condition, found in an envelope on an isotype sheet (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0FE01EAEFCFFFE5F" box="[685,819,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Perrier 1191</emphasis>
, P, barcode no. 57714). In all other respects the 
<typeStatus id="54F9885BFF82FFFF0E651E8FFC9AFE3E" box="[808,854,438,464]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0E371E8FFBCAFE3E" box="[890,1030,438,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ankarense">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0E371E8FFBCAFE3E" box="[890,1030,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. ankarense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0E581EEFFC45FE1E" box="[789,905,470,496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0E581EEFFC45FE1E" box="[789,905,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and there is no doubt that the two are conspecific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36F9FF82FFFF0FF61D2CFCA6FB87" blockId="15.[674,1212,216,1129]" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">
Although 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0E641D2CFC1CFDC1" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[809,976,533,559]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplifolium">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0E641D2CFC1CFDC1" box="[809,976,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. amplifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be regarded as a large-leaved form of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0EEC1D0CFBDBFDA1" box="[929,1047,565,591]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0EEC1D0CFBDBFDA1" box="[929,1047,565,591]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are two factors that argue against this. First, the leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0FEB1D4DFC8BFD60" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[678,839,628,654]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplifolium">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0FEB1D4DFC8BFD60" box="[678,839,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. amplifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinctly larger and do not seem to represent one extreme in a continuous range of variation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0E6B1D8DFC5BFD20" box="[806,919,692,718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0E6B1D8DFC5BFD20" box="[806,919,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Second, one does not find these large-leaved plants occasionally throughout the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0E3D1DCAFC2EFCE3" box="[880,994,755,781]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0E3D1DCAFC2EFCE3" box="[880,994,755,781]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they have instead a coherent range in a limited area of 
<collectingRegion id="4986F81BFF82FFFF094D1C2AFD1FFCA2" country="Madagascar" name="Antsiranana" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Antsiranana province</collectingRegion>
.Additional collections from the Sahafary forest, Saharenana river basin (
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0ED61C6BFBAEFC82" box="[923,1122,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">Capuron SF-24494</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF09231C6BFB7FFC82" box="[1134,1203,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">24506</emphasis>
, P), previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0EF91C4BFD38FC45" authority="(Jacques-Felix 1985 b)" baseAuthorityName="Jacques-Felix" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0EF91C4BFBEEFC62" box="[948,1058,882,908]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. perrieri</emphasis>
(Jacques-Félix 1985b)
</taxonomicName>
, are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0EDB1CABFBF1FC42" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[918,1085,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplifolium">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0EDB1CABFBF1FC42" box="[918,1085,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. amplifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except that the leaf blades are broadly oblanceolate with the bases attenuate. It may eventually be necessary to include these specimens in the circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D7AFF82FFFF0F891B29FCA3FBC4" authorityName="R. D. Stone" authorityYear="2006" box="[708,879,1040,1066]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Memecylon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="352" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amplifolium">
<emphasis id="B936EAEBFF82FFFF0F891B29FCA3FBC4" box="[708,879,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="352">M. amplifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or alternatively the Sahafary population could warrant recognition as yet another localized endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
